---
title: Steak Caprese with Mozzarella, Tomatoes, and Herbed Potatoes
description: The caprese salad is pretty impeccable as it is. Creamy mozzarella, juicy tomatoes, aromatic basil, and a resemblance to the colors of the tricolor flag—could there be a more perfect example of Italian culinary excellence? Our chefs didn’t think it could be improved upon, until they tried adding steak. The tender texture and deep flavor of thin-cut minute steaks gives the salad just what it needs to go from a side dish to a dinnertime star in its own right.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/steak-caprese-d5ede9c9.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/steak-caprese-5a7b7e5d30006c478e633a11-95122991.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
cuisine: Italian
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/steak-caprese-5a7b7e5d30006c478e633a11
nutrition:
  calories: 750 kcal
  fat: 46 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 38 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 46 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 380 mg
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into 1-inch cubes.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{1%tbsp}, @Italian seasoning{1%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

Cut @grape tomatoes{4%ounce} in half lengthwise. Cut @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce} into cubes about the same size as the tomato halves. Toss together tomatoes, mozzarella, and @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #medium bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.

Pat @minute steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season generously all over with salt and pepper. Around the same time that the potatoes are halfway done roasting (about 12 minutes after they've gone in the oven), heat @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} and @butter{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add steak and cook until browned on bottom, ~{2-3%minutes}. Flip and continue cooking until browned on other side, about ~{2%minutes} more.

Pick @basil{1/2%ounce} leaves from stems and tear into rough pieces; discard stems. Add leaves to #bowl{} with tomato and mozzarella salad and toss to combine.

Divide steak between plates, then spoon tomato and mozzarella salad over top. Drizzle with @balsamic glaze{2%tbsp} (to taste—you may not use all). Serve with potatoes on the side.